content.text:
- **Carrick Therapeutics Announces First Patient Dosed in Phase 1 Clinical Trial of CT7439 (CDK12/13 Inhibitor)**  
  **URL:** `https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/news-media/press-releases/detail/25/carrick-therapeutics-announces-first-patient-dosed-in-phase`  
  **Direct quote snippets (identifiers/targets/modalities/indications):**  
  > “CT7439, a novel cyclin dependent kinase 12/13 (CDK12/13) inhibitor / Cyclin-K glue-degrader.” ([carricktherapeutics.com](https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/news-media/press-releases/detail/25/carrick-therapeutics-announces-first-patient-dosed-in-phase))  
  > “Clinical trial details can also be found on www.clinicaltrials.gov under study ID: NCT06600789.” ([carricktherapeutics.com](https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/news-media/press-releases/detail/25/carrick-therapeutics-announces-first-patient-dosed-in-phase))  
  > “advanced solid tumors, including ovarian, breast and Ewing's Sarcoma.” ([carricktherapeutics.com](https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/news-media/press-releases/detail/25/carrick-therapeutics-announces-first-patient-dosed-in-phase))  

- **Carrick Therapeutics Announces U.S. FDA Clearance of IND for CT7439, a First-In-Class Inhibitor of CDK12/13**  
  **URL:** `https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2023/09/07/2739242/0/en/Carrick-Therapeutics-Announces-U-S-FDA-Clearance-of-IND-for-CT7439-a-First-In-Class-Inhibitor-of-CDK12-13.html`  
  **Direct quote snippets (identifiers/targets/modalities/indications):**  
  > “the Company’s Investigational New Drug (IND) application for CT7439, a novel cyclin dependent kinase 12/13 (CDK12/13) inhibitor.” ([globenewswire.com](https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2023/09/07/2739242/0/en/Carrick-Therapeutics-Announces-U-S-FDA-Clearance-of-IND-for-CT7439-a-First-In-Class-Inhibitor-of-CDK12-13.html))  
  > “CT7439 is an inhibitor of CDK12/13 as well as a 'glue degrader' of Cyclin-K” ([globenewswire.com](https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2023/09/07/2739242/0/en/Carrick-Therapeutics-Announces-U-S-FDA-Clearance-of-IND-for-CT7439-a-First-In-Class-Inhibitor-of-CDK12-13.html))  
  > “advanced solid tumors, including breast, ovarian and Ewing's Sarcoma.” ([globenewswire.com](https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2023/09/07/2739242/0/en/Carrick-Therapeutics-Announces-U-S-FDA-Clearance-of-IND-for-CT7439-a-First-In-Class-Inhibitor-of-CDK12-13.html))  

- **Carrick Therapeutics Announces First Patient Dosed in Phase 1 Clinical Trial of CT7439 (CDK12/13 Inhibitor)**  
  **URL:** `https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2024/09/23/2951333/0/en/Carrick-Therapeutics-Announces-First-Patient-Dosed-in-Phase-1-Clinical-Trial-of-CT7439-CDK12-13-Inhibitor.html`  
  **Direct quote snippets (identifiers/targets/modalities/indications):**  
  > “Phase 1 clinical trial evaluating CT7439, a novel cyclin dependent kinase 12/13 (CDK12/13) inhibitor / Cyclin-K glue-degrader.” ([globenewswire.com](https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2024/09/23/2951333/0/en/Carrick-Therapeutics-Announces-First-Patient-Dosed-in-Phase-1-Clinical-Trial-of-CT7439-CDK12-13-Inhibitor.html))  
  > “The clinical trial is enrolling patients with advanced solid tumors, including ovarian, breast and Ewing's Sarcoma.” ([globenewswire.com](https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2024/09/23/2951333/0/en/Carrick-Therapeutics-Announces-First-Patient-Dosed-in-Phase-1-Clinical-Trial-of-CT7439-CDK12-13-Inhibitor.html))  
  > “study ID: NCT06600789.” ([globenewswire.com](https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2024/09/23/2951333/0/en/Carrick-Therapeutics-Announces-First-Patient-Dosed-in-Phase-1-Clinical-Trial-of-CT7439-CDK12-13-Inhibitor.html))  

- **Trial | NCT06600789 (Clinical Drug Experience Knowledgebase, Purdue)**

  **Direct quote snippets (identifiers/targets/modalities/indications):**  
  > “Trial | NCT06600789” ([cdek.pharmacy.purdue.edu](https://cdek.pharmacy.purdue.edu/trial/NCT06600789/))  
  > “A Modular Phase 1/2 Study With CT7439 in Participants With Solid Malignancies” ([cdek.pharmacy.purdue.edu](https://cdek.pharmacy.purdue.edu/trial/NCT06600789/))  
  > “CT7439 Capsules (0.5 mg, 1mg, 3mg)” ([cdek.pharmacy.purdue.edu](https://cdek.pharmacy.purdue.edu/trial/NCT06600789/))
